Chronic sleep deprivation not only affects mood and concentration but also poses serious risks to heart health.
A study revealed that just five nights of inadequate sleep can lead to impaired heart function and increased cardiovascular disease risk.
Research from Japan and the US highlighted the negative impact of sleep deficits on heart health, with early risers at higher risk.
Athletes and children are also affected by lack of sleep, impacting performance and overall well-being.
Memory consolidation, weight gain, and hypertension are among the many health issues linked to sleep deprivation, emphasizing the importance of quality rest for optimal health.
